    "The curse of dimensionality refers to the challenges and limitations faced by machine learning models when dealing with high-dimensional data, such as increased computational complexity and data sparsity.",
    "What is the purpose of weight initialization in neural networks?",
    "Weight initialization initializes the weights of the neural network's connections to appropriate values to prevent vanishing or exploding gradients during training and accelerate convergence.",
    "What is the role of learning rate scheduling in deep learning?",
    "Learning rate scheduling dynamically adjusts the learning rate during training to improve convergence and stability, allowing the model to navigate the optimization landscape more effectively.",
    "What is the difference between online learning and batch learning?",
    "In online learning, the model is updated incrementally after processing each individual data point, while in batch learning, the model is updated after processing a fixed-size batch of data samples.",
    "What is the purpose of data normalization in deep learning?",
    "Data normalization scales the input features to a similar range or distribution, which helps to stabilize the training process, prevent numerical instability, and accelerate convergence.",
    "What is the role of momentum in gradient descent optimization?",
    "Momentum accelerates the optimization process by adding a fraction of the previous update to the current update, enabling the model to overcome small local optima and navigate the optimization landscape more efficiently.",   "What is the difference between a feedforward neural network and a recurrent neural network?",
    "A feedforward neural network processes input data in a single forward pass without any loops, while a recurrent neural network maintains a hidden state to process sequential data by incorporating information from previous time steps.",
