    "Padding is used in convolutional neural networks to preserve spatial dimensions and prevent information loss during convolution operations, ensuring that the output size matches the input size.",
    "What is the difference between a hyperparameter and a parameter in deep learning?",
    "Hyperparameters are settings or configurations that control the learning process, such as learning rate and batch size, while parameters are the internal variables (weights and biases) learned by the model during training.",
    "What is the purpose of early stopping in deep learning?",
    "Early stopping is a regularization technique used to prevent overfitting by monitoring the model's performance on a validation set and stopping the training process when the performance starts to degrade.",
    "What is the role of batch normalization in deep learning?",
    "Batch normalization normalizes the activations of each layer in a neural network by adjusting the mean and variance of mini-batches during training, which helps to stabilize and accelerate the training process.",
